<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="144" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1279,511,538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsalia present, integument with wrinkled lineation, glandularia slightly developed,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">genital acetabula relatively small and distinctly separated, P-2 ventrodistal projection moderately long and bearing two fine setae, P-3 ventral margin straight, longer than P-2, P-4 shorter than P-3, with proximal tubercle and peg-like seta slightly larger than posterior ones, excretory pore not sclerotized, leg claws with three clawlets.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,491,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Description. Both sexes.</emphasis>
Colour yellow to reddish brown. Idiosoma oval and somewhat flattened. Integument with wrinkled lineation. Idiosomal chaetome typical for the family 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tuzovskij 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Tuzovskij" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[971,1335,691,717]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Sperchontidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[1146,1326,691,717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" refId="ref3990" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (1987) Morfologiya i postembrional'noe razvitiye vodyanykh kleshchej [Morphology and Postembryonic Development in Water Mites]. Nauka Publ., Moscow, 172 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1987">Tuzovskij 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[160,226,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with five pairs of dorsocentralia. Two anterior pairs of dorsocentral plates (dc.1 and dc.2) located lateral to trichobothria 
<emphasis box="[336,364,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Oi</emphasis>
, other three pairs of dorsocentral plates (dc.3–dc.5) occupy a central position, dc.1 occasionally separated in two parts. Both pairs of trichobothria (
<emphasis box="[785,816,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fp</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[873,901,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Oi</emphasis>
) placed on small sclerites. Glandularia slightly developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1384,871,898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Anterior coxal groups with rounded medial margins and well separated, apodemes not developed (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1371,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Sclerites bearing setae 
<emphasis box="[460,493,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Hv</emphasis>
situated near posterolateral angles of coxae II. Posterior coxal groups widely separated, medial parts of coxae III narrow; glandularia 
<emphasis box="[740,770,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Pe</emphasis>
open at anteromedial margin of coxae III. Setae 
<emphasis box="[1327,1352,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Pi</emphasis>
not associated with glandularia. Excretory pore without sclerotized ring, located anterior to setae 
<emphasis box="[1175,1226,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Ci, s</emphasis>
etae 
<emphasis box="[1278,1300,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Si</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1355,1381,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Se</emphasis>
posterolateral. There is one pair of ventral platelets situated laterally between setae 
<emphasis box="[1053,1079,1016,1042]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Ci</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1136,1162,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Se</emphasis>
. Pregenital sclerite very small, postgenital sclerite comparatively large, elongate and unsclerotized. Genital field situated between posterior coxal groups, with three pairs of subequal acetabula which are distinctly separated (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1193,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Figs 3</figureCitation>
). Internal margins of genital flaps convex and cover only the second pair of acetabula completely. Each flap with 12–15 median and three to five fine lateral setae. Preginital sclerite very small, postgenital sclerite comparative large, somewhat elongate and unsclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Capitulum (
<figureCitation box="[333,399,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) with moderately long rostrum, ventral margin of rostrum convex. Both pairs of hypostomal setae subequal in length. Chelicera with large basal segment, chela crescent-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1167,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Pedipalp (
<figureCitation box="[314,374,1303,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig.7</figureCitation>
) stout, P-1 short and without setae; P-2 large, with six to eight stout dorsal setae, ventrodistal projecting moderately long conic and bearing two fine setae; P-3 moderately large maximum height near middle of segment, ventral margin straight longer than P-2, with three to five thick and two to four thin dorsal setae; P-4 slender and a little shorter than P-3, with several rather long dorsodistal and ventrodistal fine setae, ventral margin with two small tubercles bearing short peg-like seta each, proximal tubercle and peg-like seta a little larger than posterior ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Legs slender, especially posterior pair, III–IV-Leg-3–5 with several rather long dorsal plumose dorsal setae (
<figureCitation box="[160,227,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Leg claws (
<figureCitation box="[375,441,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with three unequal, pointed clawlets,`dorsal clawlet longest, dorsal and median clawlets relatively thin, ventral clawlet with broad base and shorter than the anterior ones. Claw lamella well developed with concave ventral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1663,1689]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Male.</emphasis>
Ejaculatory complex proximal chamber large, proximal arms curved, broadest basally, tapering gradually to apex, distal arms slightly convex (
<figureCitation box="[563,633,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Measurement(n=5). Idiosoma L 730–950; capitulum L 185–230, rostrum L 60–78; genital flap L 180–205, genital acetabula (ac.1–ac.3) L: 30–42, 42–48, 30–42; cheliceral segments: base L 185–215, chela L 65–70; pedipalp segments (P-1–5) L: 30–40, 120–145, 160–180, 135–155, 25–30; legs segments L: I-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 105– 130, 105–125, 145–180, 160–190, 160–190; II-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 110–140, 115–125, 170–205, 185–230, 180–215; III-Leg-1–6: 65–80, 110–145, 120–150, 175–220, 205–255, 185–235; IV-Leg-1–6: 120–165, 160–195, 145–180, 260–235, 245–295, 220–260.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1393,1951,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Female.</emphasis>
External morphology similar to male but larger, anterior genital sclerite much larger than in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Measurement (n=10). Idiosoma L 810–1300; genital flap L 185–215, genital acetabula (ac.1–ac.3) L: 35–54, 36–48, 36–48; capitulum L 210–245, rostrum L 70–80; cheliceral segments: base L 195–215, chela L 60–75; pedipalp segments (P-1–5) L: 32–45, 130–140, 170–190, 135–170, 27–32; legs segments: I-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 120–130, 110–115, 170–180, 195–205, 180–195; II-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 120–140, 129–130, 210–220, 220–230, 195–215; III- Leg-1–6: 65–80, 130–140, 130–150, 225–245, 250–270, 220–240; IV-Leg-1–6: 135–165, 175–205, 160–190, 310– 335, 285–310, 245–285.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" box="[199,893,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,362,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Deutonymph.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[416,611,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" refId="ref4028" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (1990) Opredelitel' deitonimphs vodyanykh kleschey [Key to water mite deutonymphs]. Nauka, Moscow, 238 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1990">Tuzovskij (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[653,885,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[653,885,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sperchon tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" box="[199,810,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,279,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Larva.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[333,528,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref4100" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (2006) Description of the water mite larva Sperchon tridentatus Sokolow (Acariformes. Sperchontidae). Zoologia bespozvonochnykh [Zoology invertebrates], 3 (1), 33 - 40. [in Russian] https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / invertzool. 03.1.03" type="journal article" year="2006">Tuzovskij (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[570,803,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[570,803,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sperchon tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[659,809,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[659,809,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2003" box="[865,961,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[865,961,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Tuzovskij, 2021" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2021" box="[976,1153,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pesici" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[976,1153,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sperchon pesici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1161,1222,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of the genital field and coxal plates, differences between the two species are found in the following characters (character states of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[607,756,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[607,756,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given in parentheses, data from 
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow, I. I." box="[1123,1291,475,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" pagination="1 - 511" refId="ref3946" refString="Sokolow, I. I. (1940) [Hydracarina. Part I: Hydrachnellae. In: Fauna of the USSR. Paukoobraznye 5 (2). Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, pp. 1 - 511. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1940">Sokolow 1940</bibRefCitation>
): integument with muscle attachment sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[529,627,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
) (without muscle attachment sclerites,); P-2 distoventral projecting with two fine setae, (
<figureCitation box="[334,403,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) (with three setae, 
<figureCitation box="[624,709,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); P-3 is stockier, maximum height near middle of segment (P-3 more slender, maximum height in proximal quarter); leg claws with three unequal clawlets, lamella ventral margin concave, 
<figureCitation box="[257,322,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
(leg claws with three subequal clawlets, lamella ventral margin straight, 
<figureCitation box="[1140,1224,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
The integument in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2003" box="[409,504,655,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[409,504,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with muscle attachment sclerites, dc.1 and dc.2 unsclerotized, dc.3 fused with glandulartia 
<emphasis box="[245,279,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sci</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[297,382,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), P-2 distoventral projecting short and without fine setae, with single thick seta near base of projection (
<figureCitation box="[280,364,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), ac.2 larger than ac.1 and ac.3, all acetabula slightly separated, excretory pore (
<figureCitation box="[1263,1344,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) sclerotized (
<bibRefCitation author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[220,401,763,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" pagination="215 - 219" refId="ref4060" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (2003) Two new species of water mites of the genus Sperchon Kramer (Acariformes, Sperchontidae) from Central Asia. Acarina, 11 (2), 215 - 219." type="journal article" year="2003">Tuzovskij 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" box="[199,924,799,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
